aspro
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:??Obs. Used in various usu. derog. or dismissive collocations. 1. aspro headache, a person tiresome enough to give even an aspro a headache.  2. A dismissive c.p.:  hang around and I'll fry you an aspro (aspirin), said to a tiresome person.  ca1945 p.c. students and nurses (Wellington)  3. aspro doctor, a lazy or unknowledgeable GP; a quack.  ca1935 p.c. Marlborough  from the easy prescription for all ills `Take an aspro and go to bed: seven-and-six please.'
